Actor.title: Actor
Actor.description: Can represent any model object with a foreign key to Actor.

AuthenticationContext.title: AuthenticationContext
AuthenticationContext.description: The default of all values should be a valid, non authenticated context.

ImportKind.title: ImportKind
ImportKind.description:
When importing a given model, we may create a new copy of it (`Inserted`), merely re-use an
`Existing` copy that has the same already-used globally unique identifier (ex: `username` for
users, `slug` for orgs, etc), or do an `Overwrite` that merges the new data into an existing
model that already has a `pk` assigned to it. This information can then be saved alongside the
new `pk` for the model in the `PrimaryKeyMap`, so that models that depend on this one can know
if they are dealing with a new or re-used model.

RpcEffectiveGrantStatus.title: RpcEffectiveGrantStatus
RpcEffectiveGrantStatus.description: Simplified model for access control - only contains essential, aggregated grant information.

RpcExportOk.title: RpcExportOk
RpcExportOk.description:
Information about a successful export: the mapping of old pks to new ones, the maximum pk
exported, and the JSON string of the exported models.

RpcExportScope.title: RpcExportScope
RpcExportScope.description:
Scope values are rendered as strings for JSON interchange, but can easily be mapped back to
their set-based values when necessary.

RpcFilter.title: RpcFilter
RpcFilter.description: Shadows `sentry.backup.helpers.Filter` for the purpose of passing it over an RPC boundary.

RpcImportFlags.title: RpcImportFlags
RpcImportFlags.description: Shadows `sentry.backup.helpers.ImportFlags` for the purpose of passing it over an RPC boundary.

RpcImportOk.title: RpcImportOk
RpcImportOk.description:
Information about a successful import: the mapping of old pks to new ones, the maximum pk
imported, and the total number of imported models.

RpcImportScope.title: RpcImportScope
RpcImportScope.description: Scope values are rendered as strings for JSON interchange, but can easily be mapped back to their set-based values when necessary.

RpcOrganizationSummary.title: RpcOrganizationSummary
RpcOrganizationSummary.description: The subset of organization metadata available from the control silo specifically.

RpcPrimaryKeyMap.title: RpcPrimaryKeyMap
RpcPrimaryKeyMap.description:
Shadows `sentry.backup.dependencies.PrimaryKeyMap` for the purpose of passing it over an RPC
boundary. The primary difference between this class and the one it shadows is that the original
`PrimaryKeyMap` uses `defaultdict` for ergonomics purposes, whereas this one uses a regular dict
but provides no mutation methods - it is only intended for data interchange, and should be
converted to and from `PrimaryKeyMap` immediately on either side of the RPC call.

RpcRegionUser.title: RpcRegionUser
RpcRegionUser.description:
Represents user information that may be propagated to each region that a user belongs to, often to make
more performant queries on organization member information.

RpcSentryAppService.title: RpcSentryAppService
RpcSentryAppService.description:
A `SentryAppService` (a notification service) wrapped up and serializable via the
rpc interface.

RpcUserInviteContext.title: RpcUserInviteContext
RpcUserInviteContext.description:
A context containing an intended organization member object as a potential invite, and the true
inner organization member state as found for a given user_id if it exists, or just the organization
member state of the invite if none such exists.

RpcUserOrganizationContext.title: RpcUserOrganizationContext
RpcUserOrganizationContext.description:
This object wraps an organization result inside of its membership context in terms of an (optional) user id.
This is due to the large number of callsites that require an organization and a user's membership at the
same time and in a consistency state.  This object allows a nice envelop for both of these ideas from a single
transactional query.  Used by access, determine_active_organization, and others.

RpcUserProfile.title: RpcUserProfile
RpcUserProfile.description: Minimal set of user attributes that can be fetched efficiently.
